ased on similarity) used to be claimed to be an alternative to <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cladistics\" rel=\"nofollow\">cladistics<\/a>, but now it is widely accepted that phenetic analyses cannot be used to infer evolutionary relationships. However, phenetic methods like neighbor-joining trees are still being developed today. <\/p>\n\n<p>Are phenetic analyses still valid today for purposes other than determining evolutionary relationships, or are they completely obsolete? Does anyone have an example of a recent paper that uses phenetic analyses in a valid way?<\/p>\n","question_id":31348,"tags":["phylogenetics","history"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":15,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b06e99ad7973cd2a998bf2008950cb2f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":8569,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8569/theo","reputation":36,"display_name":"Theo"},"closed_date":1407318484,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":1,"post_id":20117,"edited":false,"creation_date":1406894003,"comment_id":30153,"body":"Wikipedia is fairly decent :P"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/L9Qqu.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5784,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5784/5heikki","reputation":428,"display_name":"5heikki"},"score":5,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4ad1bf5323f1d059639a3d13bcbf8121?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":8574,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8574/kris-harper","reputation":101,"display_name":"Kris Harper"},"score":0,"post_id":20124,"edited":false,"creation_date":1406900295,"comment_