>As you lose salt and other minerals the water you consume begins to build up in your cells via diffusion<\/li>\n<li>You can either die of not enough energy or lack of protein or too many cells disintegrate from too much water<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>Source(s) : Biology book, Internet, Knowledge.<\/p>\n","answer_id":31272,"question_id":31235,"up_vote_count":0}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/31235/survival-with-only-water-but-no-food","last_activity_date":1428827194,"creation_date":1428709807,"answer_count":1,"title":"Survival with only water but no food","body":"<p>How long can the average, healthy adult human survive with only water? <\/p>\n","question_id":31235,"tags":["human-biology"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":1,"closed_reason":"duplicate","is_answered":false,"view_count":98,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1428720412},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e8070d717466a78c495dea88e6ecb108?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":9524,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9524/so2","reputation":8,"display_name":"so2"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":31231,"edited":false,"creation_date":1428692010,"comment_id":52216,"body":"What do you mean by &quot;non-infectious diseases&quot;? The white blood cells are part of the adaptive immune system and play a very important role to keep us healthy."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e8070d717466a78c495dea88e6ecb108?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":9524,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9524/so2","reputation":8,"display_name":"so2"},"score":0,"post_id":31231,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bf