-cells, and NK cells, so a huge part of their immune system is defective), but I cannot find anything about cancer or cardiovascular diseases by them. They are usually engrafted with human cancer, etc... in the experiments, which is not the same as naturally developing cancer. Maybe if you have time to google a day or two, you can find more.<\/p>\n\n<p>Be aware that there are many different types of leukocytes (WBCs), which have their own role in the immune system. Some of the people with leukopenia have lack only of a single type of leukocytes and not all of them. For example HIV patients have helper T-cell deficiency, people with neutropenia have neutrophil granulocyte deficiency, and so on...<\/p>\n\n<p>I don't know anything of the treatment, I guess bone marrow transplant is involved in the severe cases. If it is caused by medication as a side effect, or you are seeking for medical advice, I think you should consult a doctor.<\/p>\n","answer_id":31266,"question_id":31231,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/jlp4Q.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5198,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5198/anongoodnurse","reputation":12148,"display_name":"anongoodnurse"},"score":1,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e8070d717466a78c495dea88e6ecb108?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":9524,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9524/so2","reputation":8,"display_name":"so2"},"score":0,"post_id":31271,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429035866,"comment_id":52423,"body":"Thanks for the detailed answer! Biopsy done by a hematologist some years ago didn&#39;t provide any actionable diagnosis. Since an accompanying blood test coincidentally revealed liver enzyme imbalance, was redirected to a gastroenterologist to check if liver is affected and causing low WBC as side-effect. Liver found to be normal now but WBC still low as it was years ag