03,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3703/inf3rno","reputation":2903,"display_name":"inf3rno","accept_rate":50},"score":0,"post_id":31265,"edited":false,"creation_date":1428802029,"comment_id":52278,"body":"I think you should check rRNA synthesis regulation: <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/cdd/journal/v20/n11/images/cdd2013107f1.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\">nature.com/cdd/journal/v20/n11/images/cdd2013107f1.jpg<\/a> . So it seems to be regulated by sensing stress and not the ribosome damage directly. Another possible mechanism to measure the mRNA synthesis rate and if it is too high, then build a new ribosome. Maybe there is something like that too in the background, I don&#39;t know, interesting question."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fcf9d3bdac2c3fa35177730c31b34f79?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6307/canadianer","reputation":6147,"display_name":"canadianer"},"score":1,"post_id":31265,"edited":false,"creation_date":1428817508,"comment_id":52281,"body":"I&#39;m unaware of any repair mechanisms. Damaged proteins and RNA are usually dealt with by degradation."}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/31265/is-there-a-cellular-mechanism-that-detects-ribosomal-damage","last_activity_date":1428798304,"creation_date":1428798304,"answer_count":0,"title":"Is there a cellular mechanism that detects Ribosomal damage?","body":"<p>What kinds of options, if any, do cells (Eukary and Prokary) have for detecting, and repairing damage in Ribosomes (of all types)? I am curious as to \nwhat happens when a cell sustains damage of some form, such as radiation, and the Ribosomes are damaged. <\/p>\n","question_id":31265,"tags":["proteins","rna","amino-acids","ribosome"],"score":3,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":25,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Lq8l9.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_i