.edu/hjakubowski/classes/ch331/oxphos/olphotsynthesis.html\">webpage<\/a>, which gives a good introduction.<\/p>\n","answer_id":31195,"question_id":31192,"up_vote_count":5}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/31192/what-goes-on-in-photosystems-at-the-molecular-atomic-level","last_activity_date":1428574352,"creation_date":1428572642,"answer_count":1,"title":"What Goes on in Photosystems at the Molecular/Atomic Level?","body":"<p>In light-harvesting complexes, how is the energy of a photon transferred from one pigment molecule to another? And in reaction-center complexes, how does the primary electron acceptor capture an electron from the chlorophyll <em>a<\/em>? It\u2019d be best if any of you could explain this to me in terms of what\u2019s happening at the molecular or atomic level, say with electrons.<\/p>\n","question_id":31192,"tags":["biochemistry","photosynthesis"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":31195,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":45,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1428572766},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f61424120ea62d14072faafff46802f6?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4477,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4477/bob","reputation":8,"display_name":"Bob"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/08613e0b782cdf2bb8f2501cae9bdc5d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":806,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/806/armatus","reputation":5317,"display_name":"Armatus","accept_rate":81},"score":0,"post_id":10466,"edited":false,"creation_date":1379369437,"comment_id":13826,"body":"Is this a question about a real case? Or are you possibly asking about a homework question? (It sounds kind of like that to me)"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f61424120ea62d14072faafff46802f6?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4477,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/u