 color you might have asked, as stated <a href=\"https://books.google.hu/books?id=yHHABAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA23&amp;lpg=PA23&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=Z1Dnt36iMe&amp;sig=I_9Y7KxhsJBDlJvuTeNRyjdf4aY&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=6-oiVf_4H4bYsAWqwoCQCA&amp;redir_esc=y#v=onepage&amp;q=bright%20red&amp;f=false\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a> on page 39:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>The first manifestation of livor mortis can be expected 20-30 min following the irreversible cardiovascular arrest, initially as bright-red spots that subsequently become confluent and turn bluish-violet.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Which might better describe your case is the fact, that cold conditions can cause bright red color in livor mortis, as it can also be found on page 39:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Cold conditions, such as keeping a body in cold storage, cause ... bright-red livor mortis.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>You can read more about it <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Livor_mortis\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a> or <a href=\"http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/livor+mortis\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>EDIT<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>I have added references thanks to @Kendall, who provided them.<\/p>\n","answer_id":31106,"question_id":23062,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1428375956}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/23062/formaldehyde-turns-plantar-region-of-feet-red","last_activity_date":1428375956,"creation_date":1413115025,"answer_count":1,"title":"Formaldehyde turns plantar region of feet red?","body":"<p>I'm a freshman med student and I've noticed that on all the feet (and hands) of deceased people that I've worked with, the bottom of the feet always turns red and also the inside of the palm? Why is this?<\/p>\n\n<p>Thank you.<\/p>\n","question_id":23062,"tags":["biochemistry","medicine","decay"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":31106,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":136,"up_vote_count":5},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://